Great Scott!

01:03.188 --> 01:04.940
You got a letter

01:04.982 --> 01:05.941
from Martindale Academy!

01:05.983 --> 01:08.109
What's Martindale Academy?

01:08.151 --> 01:09.152
It's the greatest,

01:09.194 --> 01:11.112
most advanced private

01:09.194 --> 01:11.112
school in existence.

01:11.154 --> 01:12.531
Do you know how many

01:11.154 --> 01:12.531
millions they've spent

01:12.573 --> 01:14.157
to make sure you've

01:12.573 --> 01:14.157
never heard about it?

01:14.199 --> 01:15.993
It says I've been accepted.

01:16.035 --> 01:17.118
I didn't even apply.

01:17.160 --> 01:19.287
No one applies. They find you.

01:19.329 --> 01:20.288
This is

01:19.329 --> 01:20.288
unbelievable.

01:20.330 --> 01:22.207
Malcolm, you're going

01:20.330 --> 01:22.207
to the show.

01:22.249 --> 01:23.709
You're set for life!

01:23.751 --> 01:25.168
Wait, what am I thinking?

01:25.210 --> 01:27.128
You can't go.

01:25.210 --> 01:27.128
You're too poor.

01:27.170 --> 01:29.423
You're like the

01:27.170 --> 01:29.423
poorest guy I know.

01:29.464 --> 01:31.842
Oh, I'm such a jerk!

01:31.884 --> 01:33.510
Here I am, describing

01:31.884 --> 01:33.510
this nirvana

01:33.552 --> 01:35.178
you'll never be

01:33.552 --> 01:35.178
able to experience.

01:35.220 --> 01:37.431
Holding out this hope

01:35.220 --> 01:37.431
of power and success

01:37.472 --> 01:39.140
to a guy in

01:37.472 --> 01:39.140
a three-dollar shirt.

01:39.182 --> 01:41.226
I mean, look at this hovel!

01:41.268 --> 01:44.438
Lloyd, you have to stop talking.

01:44.479 --> 01:46.440
It's okay to cry, Malcolm.

01:46.481 --> 01:48.191
Tears are free.

01:49.902 --> 01:51.653
Okay, everybody.

01:51.695 --> 01:52.613
Just got back

01:51.695 --> 01:52.613
from the doctor

01:52.654 --> 01:54.197
and everything's fine,

01:54.239 --> 01:56.867
but baby's a little bit

01:54.239 --> 01:56.867
bigger than expected.

01:56.909 --> 01:58.744
HAL: So, instead of having

01:56.909 --> 01:58.744
the baby in two weeks

01:58.786 --> 02:00.161
like we thought, we're going

02:00.203 --> 02:01.956
to induce labor

02:00.203 --> 02:01.956
on Thursday.

02:01.997 --> 02:02.998
Thursday?!

02:03.040 --> 02:03.958
This Thursday?!

02:03.999 --> 02:05.084
You can't do that!

02:05.125 --> 02:07.044
Oh, what difference

02:05.125 --> 02:07.044
does it make?

02:07.086 --> 02:09.546
It's just six days sooner

02:07.086 --> 02:09.546
that our lives are over.

02:09.588 --> 02:11.172
Hal.

02:11.214 --> 02:14.051
And... our new,

02:11.214 --> 02:14.051
more fulfilling lives begin.

02:14.093 --> 02:15.176
This stinks.

02:15.218 --> 02:16.344
LOIS:

02:15.218 --> 02:16.344
I know this is being

02:16.386 --> 02:17.554
sprung on you very suddenly,

02:17.596 --> 02:19.347
and you all have a right

02:17.596 --> 02:19.347
to be a little upset.

02:19.389 --> 02:21.182
A little?!

02:19.389 --> 02:21.182
Don't push it.

02:21.224 --> 02:23.018
Hal, you know what?

02:21.224 --> 02:23.018
I've got an idea.

02:23.060 --> 02:24.185
Why don't you

02:23.060 --> 02:24.185
take the boys

02:24.227 --> 02:25.771
out tomorrow and

02:24.227 --> 02:25.771
do something fun?

02:25.813 --> 02:27.230
I could use the time

02:25.813 --> 02:27.230
alone anyway

02:27.272 --> 02:29.691
to straighten up the house

02:27.272 --> 02:29.691
before the baby comes.

02:29.733 --> 02:30.818
I can help

02:29.733 --> 02:30.818
you clean.

02:30.859 --> 02:32.193
Well, that'll take

02:30.859 --> 02:32.193
a little longer,

02:32.235 --> 02:34.029
but I guess I could

02:32.235 --> 02:34.029
use the company.

