HAL:

02:34.071 --> 02:35.114
Hey, there's a car show

02:35.155 --> 02:36.364
at the convention center.

02:36.406 --> 02:37.699
Yeah, let's spend the whole day

02:37.741 --> 02:39.493
looking at cool things

02:37.741 --> 02:39.493
that we'll never get to own.

02:39.534 --> 02:42.037
Oh, come on, Malcolm, if we only

02:39.534 --> 02:42.037
looked at stuff we could afford,

02:42.079 --> 02:43.413
all we'd ever

02:42.079 --> 02:43.413
see is crap.

02:43.455 --> 02:44.623
HAL:

02:43.455 --> 02:44.623
Don't be a party pooper.

02:44.665 --> 02:46.166
It'll be great.

02:47.334 --> 02:49.628
MALCOLM:

02:47.334 --> 02:49.628
"Festival of Brides"?

02:49.670 --> 02:51.630
That's the lamest

02:49.670 --> 02:51.630
name for a car show

02:49.670 --> 02:51.630
I've ever heard.

02:51.672 --> 02:53.214
No, the car show

02:51.672 --> 02:53.214
was here last week.

02:53.256 --> 02:54.424
Let's get out of here.

02:54.466 --> 02:56.844
No. I just dropped 15 bucks

02:54.466 --> 02:56.844
on parking.

02:56.885 --> 02:59.054
We're going in.

02:59.096 --> 03:00.639
I know it's your fifth child,

03:00.681 --> 03:02.933
but still, you must be

03:00.681 --> 03:02.933
a little excited.

03:02.975 --> 03:05.060
Well, sure, every

03:02.975 --> 03:05.060
child is exciting.

03:05.102 --> 03:07.186
Not that you want to rush

03:05.102 --> 03:07.186
into something like that.

03:07.896 --> 03:08.939
Oh!

03:08.981 --> 03:10.315
Wow.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.608
You okay?

03:11.650 --> 03:13.861
The baby just started

03:11.650 --> 03:13.861
kicking like crazy.

03:13.902 --> 03:15.696
It's almost

03:13.902 --> 03:15.696
like something

03:13.902 --> 03:15.696
was upsetting...

03:18.073 --> 03:19.240
Mom!

03:19.282 --> 03:21.242
Are you going to open the door

03:21.284 --> 03:24.872
or should I lie down

03:21.284 --> 03:24.872
in the grass and feed the worms?

03:24.913 --> 03:26.247
Oh, great.

03:26.289 --> 03:27.916
Who opened the gates of hell?

03:27.958 --> 03:29.877
Mom? This is a surprise.

03:29.918 --> 03:31.879
What are you doing here?

03:31.920 --> 03:34.048
I'm moving in.

03:34.089 --> 03:35.841
What do you mean

03:34.089 --> 03:35.841
you're moving in?

03:35.883 --> 03:38.468
You are family, you

03:35.883 --> 03:38.468
will take care of me.

03:38.510 --> 03:39.887
This is ridiculous.

03:39.928 --> 03:40.888
You have a condo.

03:40.929 --> 03:41.972
It's nicer than this house.

03:42.014 --> 03:43.098
It burned down.

03:43.140 --> 03:45.266
Mother, you

03:43.140 --> 03:45.266
can't just...

03:45.308 --> 03:46.560
How did your house burn down?

03:46.601 --> 03:48.228
It was the villagers,

03:46.601 --> 03:48.228
wasn't it?

03:49.354 --> 03:51.356
It's a mystery.

03:51.398 --> 03:53.274
Why don't you go stay

03:51.398 --> 03:53.274
at Susan's?

03:53.316 --> 03:56.277
She has four extra bedrooms

03:53.316 --> 03:56.277
and a satellite dish.

03:56.319 --> 03:58.279
Your sister should stick

03:56.319 --> 03:58.279
her head in a can of beans!

03:58.321 --> 03:59.280
What?!

03:59.322 --> 04:00.657
She's always been your favorite.

04:00.699 --> 04:02.492
She's the only one you called

04:00.699 --> 04:02.492
when Dad died.

04:02.534 --> 04:04.161
She isn't my favorite anymore!

04:04.203 --> 04:06.163
She called me bitter!

04:06.205 --> 04:08.123
Then she hung up on me.

04:08.165 --> 04:09.290
On me!

04:09.332 --> 04:11.126
Or maybe I hung up on her.

04:11.168 --> 04:12.669
Who remembers?

04:12.711 --> 04:15.089
Either way,

04:12.711 --> 04:15.089
she should rot in hell.

04:15.130 --> 04:17.465
Mother, we can't afford

04:15.130 --> 04:17.465
to put you up here.

04:17.507 --> 04:19.134
You can afford a maid.

04:19.176 --> 04:20.719
I'm not the maid, Ida.

04:20.761 --> 04:21.887
My name is Piama.

04:21.929 --> 04:23.555
I'm married to Francis.

04:23.597 --> 04:26.516
Tell the help

04:23.597 --> 04:26.516
not to talk to me.

04:26.558 --> 04:28.602
♪ Yahoo ♪

04:31.939 --> 04:36.818
♪ Celebrate good times,

04:31.939 --> 04:36.818
come on ♪

04:36.860 --> 04:39.154
♪ It's a celebration... ♪

04:39.196 --> 04:41.031
I know I haven't

04:39.196 --> 04:41.031
been everywhere,

04:41.073 --> 04:42.157
but I'm pretty sure

04:42.199 --> 04:44.325
this is the most

04:42.199 --> 04:44.325
boring place on Earth.

04:44.367 --> 04:46.327
What are you talking about,

04:44.367 --> 04:46.327
Reese?

04:46.369 --> 04:48.496
Do you know

04:46.369 --> 04:48.496
what kind of craftsmanship

04:48.538 --> 04:50.540
goes into these lace veils? Huh?

04:50.582 --> 04:53.127
So, uh, Dad, I

04:50.582 --> 04:53.127
was wondering,

04:53.168 --> 04:55.796
do you have any kind

04:53.168 --> 04:55.796
of savings put away?

04:56.838 --> 05:00.092
(laughing hysterically)

05:00.842 --> 05:02.970
(laughing, snorts)

05:03.011 --> 05:05.931
Ooh, I'll have to tell

05:03.011 --> 05:05.931
your mother that one.

05:05.973 --> 05:07.348
No, I'm serious.

05:07.390 --> 05:08.600
What if something came up?

05:08.642 --> 05:10.351
Like a big, unexpected expense?

05:10.393 --> 05:12.520
Are you prepared

05:10.393 --> 05:12.520
for something like that?

05:12.562 --> 05:13.981
Don't worry

05:12.562 --> 05:13.981
about that stuff, son.

05:14.022 --> 05:15.857
Things have a way

05:14.022 --> 05:15.857
of taking care of themselves.

05:15.899 --> 05:17.358
But...

05:15.899 --> 05:17.358
Come on.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.736
You boys are young.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.736
You're at a bridal expo.

05:19.778 --> 05:22.239
You should be having

05:19.778 --> 05:22.239
the time of your lives.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.365
Dewey?

05:24.407 --> 05:25.533
Dewey?

05:25.575 --> 05:27.368
What are those wires for?

05:27.410 --> 05:28.787
You see that big spotlight

05:27.410 --> 05:28.787
up there?

05:28.829 --> 05:30.538
I'm in charge

05:28.829 --> 05:30.538
of that puppy.

05:30.580 --> 05:31.372
You like it?

05:31.414 --> 05:32.833
I really do.

05:34.501 --> 05:37.420
I'd like to tell you

05:34.501 --> 05:37.420
a little story.

05:38.880 --> 05:41.258
FRANCIS (sotto voce):

05:38.880 --> 05:41.258
Are you going to let her

05:41.300 --> 05:42.383
get away with this?

05:42.425 --> 05:44.552
You are, aren't you?

05:44.594 --> 05:46.221
She's my mother.

05:46.263 --> 05:48.098
You know the way I am

05:46.263 --> 05:48.098
around her.

05:48.140 --> 05:49.390
Okay, if that's what you want.

05:49.432 --> 05:50.976
That woman being one of

05:51.018 --> 05:52.393
the first people

05:51.018 --> 05:52.393
your new baby sees

05:52.435 --> 05:53.687
when it comes

05:52.435 --> 05:53.687
into this world.

05:53.728 --> 05:56.064
Smiling down at it,

05:56.106 --> 05:58.275
cradling it in her arms.

05:58.317 --> 06:00.777
You're right.

05:58.317 --> 06:00.777
She's got to go.

06:00.819 --> 06:01.903
LOIS:

06:00.819 --> 06:01.903
Mom.

06:03.362 --> 06:05.324
There's something important

06:03.362 --> 06:05.324
that I have to tell you.

06:05.364 --> 06:07.117
What is it?

06:09.328 --> 06:11.412
You are a horrible mother!

06:11.454 --> 06:13.414
You've always been

06:11.454 --> 06:13.414
a horrible mother!

06:13.456 --> 06:14.457
My whole childhood

06:14.499 --> 06:16.001
you'd bully me and ignore me

06:16.043 --> 06:17.044
and trivialize

06:16.043 --> 06:17.044
my feelings

06:17.085 --> 06:18.419
and do nothing

06:17.085 --> 06:18.419
but heap praise

06:18.461 --> 06:21.422
on my sister until I felt like

06:18.461 --> 06:21.422
I was worthless in comparison!

06:21.464 --> 06:23.008
Well, now she's worthless.

06:23.050 --> 06:25.135
I've got a right

06:23.050 --> 06:25.135
to change my mind.

06:25.177 --> 06:28.263
But just because your sister

06:25.177 --> 06:28.263
disgusts me more than you do

06:28.305 --> 06:31.016
doesn't give you the right

06:28.305 --> 06:31.016
to talk to me like this!

06:31.058 --> 06:35.062
I will talk to you any damn way

06:31.058 --> 06:35.062
I want, you hateful old woman!

06:35.103 --> 06:36.271
You are leaving!

06:36.313 --> 06:37.522
Wow! I don't know how

06:37.564 --> 06:40.525
I finally summoned the

06:37.564 --> 06:40.525
strength to do that,

06:40.567 --> 06:41.902
but it feels great!

06:41.943 --> 06:44.696
Now I'm not asking you,

06:41.943 --> 06:44.696
I'm telling you!

06:44.738 --> 06:46.907
Get out of my house!

06:46.948 --> 06:48.950
No.

06:50.493 --> 06:51.828
What?

06:51.870 --> 06:53.955
You heard me.

06:51.870 --> 06:53.955
I said "no."

06:53.997 --> 06:55.249
What do you mean, "no"?

06:55.290 --> 06:56.666
You don't have any choice.

06:56.708 --> 06:58.459
What are you going to do?

06:58.501 --> 07:00.337
Pick me up and throw me out?

07:00.379 --> 07:03.298
Are you going to toss an old

07:00.379 --> 07:03.298
woman out into the street?

07:03.340 --> 07:05.424
In front of your neighbors?

07:06.509 --> 07:07.761
Sounds good to me.

07:07.802 --> 07:09.263
Whoa!

07:07.802 --> 07:09.263
You brought this

07:07.802 --> 07:09.263
on yourself,

07:09.304 --> 07:10.764
you old monster.

07:10.805 --> 07:12.557
You have no idea

07:10.805 --> 07:12.557
how good this makes me...

07:12.599 --> 07:13.516
(yelps)

07:22.943 --> 07:24.527
(gasping)

07:27.530 --> 07:30.784
(playing "Celebration")

07:30.825 --> 07:32.786
Attention, ladies and gentlemen.

07:32.827 --> 07:34.329
It's your "clucky" day.

07:34.371 --> 07:37.874
Chicken dance lessons are being

07:34.371 --> 07:37.874
given every ten minutes

07:37.916 --> 07:40.501
at the Fielding Dance Academy

07:37.916 --> 07:40.501
pavilion.

07:40.543 --> 07:41.920
Excuse me.

07:41.962 --> 07:45.340
Can I talk to you

07:41.962 --> 07:45.340
for a second?

07:46.591 --> 07:48.802
Hey, can you get me a piece

07:46.591 --> 07:48.802
with a flower?

07:48.843 --> 07:50.804
I'm talking

07:48.843 --> 07:50.804
to an actual customer right now.

07:50.845 --> 07:51.972
I'm a customer.

07:52.013 --> 07:54.099
Yeah?

07:52.013 --> 07:54.099
Are you getting married?

07:54.141 --> 07:55.725
Why, does somebody like me?

07:55.767 --> 07:58.312
Hey, what are you,

07:55.767 --> 07:58.312
about five-seven?

07:55.767 --> 07:58.312
Yeah.

07:58.353 --> 07:59.520
Perfect. I own a tux shop.

07:59.562 --> 08:00.730
One of my models

07:59.562 --> 08:00.730
didn't show up.

08:00.772 --> 08:02.607
I'll give you 20 bucks

08:00.772 --> 08:02.607
if you walk around

08:02.649 --> 08:04.692
the floor in a tux

08:02.649 --> 08:04.692
and pass out my card.

08:02.649 --> 08:04.692
Buzz off.

08:04.734 --> 08:06.527
20 bucks?

08:04.734 --> 08:06.527
He'll do it.

08:06.569 --> 08:08.196
Need anybody in my size?

08:09.489 --> 08:10.531
It's very simple.

08:10.573 --> 08:13.534
You just walk up to somebody,

08:10.573 --> 08:13.534
get down on one knee,

08:13.576 --> 08:15.329
hand them one of my cards

08:13.576 --> 08:15.329
and say,

08:15.370 --> 08:18.539
"I propose that you get your

08:15.370 --> 08:18.539
tuxedo from Wojodubakowski's."

08:18.581 --> 08:19.374
No problem.

