13:22.885 --> 13:24.845
they'll cut you off.

13:24.887 --> 13:26.931
You're going to be bankrupt

13:24.887 --> 13:26.931
and ruined.

13:26.973 --> 13:28.099
Something will come up.

13:28.141 --> 13:29.225
You can't keep saying that.

13:29.267 --> 13:30.851
Fine. I'm a failure

13:29.267 --> 13:30.851
as a father.

13:30.893 --> 13:32.061
I'm a terrible provider.

13:32.103 --> 13:33.854
Is that what you want to hear?

13:33.896 --> 13:36.107
No.

13:36.149 --> 13:37.900
But I have a way to fix it.

13:37.942 --> 13:39.569
What's this?

13:39.611 --> 13:42.280
It's from the Martindale

13:39.611 --> 13:42.280
Academy.

13:43.114 --> 13:45.450
It's this amazing prep school...

13:45.492 --> 13:46.993
but it's in London.

13:48.369 --> 13:50.330
They're offering me

13:48.369 --> 13:50.330
a complete scholarship.

13:50.371 --> 13:52.332
Tuition, housing,

13:52.373 --> 13:53.750
everything.

13:54.751 --> 13:56.377
If I'm not home...

13:56.419 --> 13:58.546
you just might make it.

13:58.588 --> 14:00.590
I'm totally willing to do it.

14:02.925 --> 14:05.303
Absolutely not.

14:05.345 --> 14:07.347
You don't get to leave.

14:07.388 --> 14:09.098
But you...

14:07.388 --> 14:09.098
Malcolm, you're our only hope.

14:09.140 --> 14:10.891
Hold this.

14:09.140 --> 14:10.891
Sure.

14:10.933 --> 14:12.560
Now let me explain

14:10.933 --> 14:12.560
something to you.

14:12.602 --> 14:14.187
Whenever your mother or I say

14:14.228 --> 14:16.523
"Something will come up"

14:14.228 --> 14:16.523
or "Things will work out,"

14:16.564 --> 14:19.900
that is our code for "Malcolm

14:16.564 --> 14:19.900
will think of something."

14:19.942 --> 14:21.569
But...

14:19.942 --> 14:21.569
We need you.

14:21.611 --> 14:23.279
The family is only a family

14:23.321 --> 14:25.532
as long as we all

14:23.321 --> 14:25.532
stick together.

14:26.949 --> 14:28.868
Where's Dewey?

14:32.622 --> 14:33.998
(dramatic accordion music plays)

14:34.040 --> 14:36.626
ANNOUNCER:

14:34.040 --> 14:36.626
Ladies and gentlemen,

14:34.040 --> 14:36.626
if you'll please

14:36.668 --> 14:38.919
turn your attention

14:36.668 --> 14:38.919
to the man with the balloon,

14:38.961 --> 14:40.755
and listen to the following

14:40.797 --> 14:42.882
heart-wrenching story.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.637
Hello. My name is Dewey.

14:47.679 --> 14:51.766
And the man with the balloon

14:47.679 --> 14:51.766
is my father, Hal.

14:51.808 --> 14:52.767
Dewey?

14:52.809 --> 14:53.934
Where are you?

14:53.976 --> 14:54.935
See,

14:54.977 --> 14:56.937
I'm the youngest

14:54.977 --> 14:56.937
of four kids,

14:56.979 --> 14:59.816
and I always get

14:56.979 --> 14:59.816
the short end

14:56.979 --> 14:59.816
of everything.

14:59.858 --> 15:03.944
I've never had a hot shower

14:59.858 --> 15:03.944
or a bed to myself.

15:03.986 --> 15:05.946
I'm the third person

15:03.986 --> 15:05.946
to wear this underwear.

15:05.988 --> 15:08.949
And yet, I've

15:05.988 --> 15:08.949
never complained.

15:08.991 --> 15:10.951
Dewey, what is this about?!

15:10.993 --> 15:14.955
Even when my parents decided

15:10.993 --> 15:14.955
to have another baby.

15:14.997 --> 15:16.165
I was happy to share

15:16.207 --> 15:17.458
what little I have.

15:17.500 --> 15:20.961
And then they told me

15:17.500 --> 15:20.961
they're inducing labor.

15:21.003 --> 15:24.965
And they picked a really

15:21.003 --> 15:24.965
interesting day to do it.

15:25.007 --> 15:27.968
Do you remember what day

15:25.007 --> 15:27.968
you picked, Dad?

15:28.010 --> 15:29.053
Dewey!

15:29.095 --> 15:31.765
What day did you pick, Dad?

15:31.806 --> 15:32.973
It's Thursday.

15:33.015 --> 15:35.268
Just come down from...

15:33.015 --> 15:35.268
wherever you are.

15:35.309 --> 15:37.812
Of all the days

15:35.309 --> 15:37.812
you could have picked,

15:37.854 --> 15:39.814
you chose

15:37.854 --> 15:39.814
this Thursday.

15:39.856 --> 15:42.776
Anything interesting

15:39.856 --> 15:42.776
about Thursday, Dad?

15:42.817 --> 15:44.652
Will you stop this?

15:44.694 --> 15:46.362
Anything at all

15:44.694 --> 15:46.362
you can think of

15:46.404 --> 15:48.573
that might be happening

15:46.404 --> 15:48.573
this Thursday?

15:48.615 --> 15:51.992
Okay, Dewey, what is

15:48.615 --> 15:51.992
the big deal about Thursday?

15:52.034 --> 15:55.371
(echoing):

15:52.034 --> 15:55.371
It's my birthday.

15:55.413 --> 15:57.498
(gasping)

15:57.540 --> 15:59.500
It is not your...

15:59.542 --> 16:01.961
Oh, God!

16:03.129 --> 16:05.256
Well, ladies

16:03.129 --> 16:05.256
and gentleman...

16:05.298 --> 16:07.717
that's the story

16:05.298 --> 16:07.717
of the little boy

16:07.759 --> 16:09.719
who lost his birthday.

16:09.761 --> 16:12.012
If you have any thoughts

16:09.761 --> 16:12.012
or comments,

16:12.054 --> 16:14.014
